Code Explanation:
Imported Packages:

fmt: To display messages on the console.
net/http: To handle HTTP requests.
Handler:

The handler function is called every time a request is made to the server. It writes "Hello, World!" to the response.
Server:

http.HandleFunc("/") associates the handler function with the path /.
http.ListenAndServe(":8080", nil) starts the server on port 8080.

How to Run:
Save the code in a file called main.go.
In the terminal, run:
go run main.go
Go to http://localhost:8080 in your browser to see the result.